From: MLIR Python bindings Emscripten init
Subject: [PATCH 0007] Add mlir/__init__.py: Emscripten shared-library preloader

Adds mlir/python/mlir/__init__.py (entirely guarded by
`if sys.platform == "emscripten"`) to pre-load the three MLIR shared
libraries before any extension module's dlopen triggers neededDynlib
resolution.

Background: Emscripten's LDSO resolves neededDynlibs by short name,
searching /lib/, but ctypes.CDLL with a full path registers the library
under that full path as its key.  When libMLIRPythonSupport-mlir.so later
requests libnanobind-mlir.so as a dependency the short-name lookup fails
with "need to see wasm magic number".  Fix: create /lib/<name> symlinks
(cheap in MEMFS) and load via those paths.

diff --git a/mlir/python/CMakeLists.txt b/mlir/python/CMakeLists.txt
--- a/mlir/python/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/mlir/python/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -24,6 +24,7 @@ declare_mlir_python_sources(MLIRPythonSources.Core.Python
   ROOT_DIR "${CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/mlir"
   ADD_TO_PARENT MLIRPythonSources.Core
   SOURCES
+    __init__.py
     _mlir_libs/__init__.py
     _mlir_libs/_mlir/py.typed
     ir.py

diff --git a/mlir/python/mlir/__init__.py b/mlir/python/mlir/__init__.py
new file mode 100644
--- /dev/null
+++ b/mlir/python/mlir/__init__.py
@@ -0,0 +1,45 @@
+"""
+MLIR Python bindings package initializer.
+
+On Emscripten/JupyterLite, pre-loads the MLIR shared libraries before any
+extension module import triggers neededDynlib resolution.
+
+Background: Emscripten's dynamic linker (LDSO) resolves neededDynlibs by
+short name (e.g. ``libnanobind-mlir.so``), searching directories like
+``/lib/``.  But ``ctypes.CDLL`` with a full path registers the library under
+that full path as its key, so when ``libMLIRPythonSupport-mlir.so`` later
+tries to load ``libnanobind-mlir.so`` as a dependency, the short-name lookup
+fails with "need to see wasm magic number".
+
+Fix: create ``/lib/<name>`` symlinks (cheap in MEMFS — just a directory
+entry) and load the libraries via those symlink paths, so that they are
+registered under both their short name and full path.
+"""
+
+import sys
+
+if sys.platform == "emscripten":
+    import ctypes
+    import os
+
+    _libs_dir = os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), "_mlir_libs")
+
+    for _lib in (
+        "libnanobind-mlir.so",
+        "libMLIRPythonCAPI.so.22.1",
+        "libMLIRPythonSupport-mlir.so",
+    ):
+        _src = os.path.join(_libs_dir, _lib)
+        _dst = f"/lib/{_lib}"
+        if os.path.exists(_src) and not os.path.exists(_dst):
+            try:
+                os.symlink(_src, _dst)
+            except OSError:
+                pass
+
+    for _lib in (
+        "libnanobind-mlir.so",
+        "libMLIRPythonCAPI.so.22.1",
+        "libMLIRPythonSupport-mlir.so",
+    ):
+        _p = f"/lib/{_lib}"
+        if os.path.exists(_p):
+            ctypes.CDLL(_p, ctypes.RTLD_GLOBAL)
